Decibel continued to glower at Tumult until Darkfate's voice cut in,
the tone of it caused Decibel's glower to be turned on Darkfate.
"Hmmph! With names like yours I would have thought you were spies or
something. Dark? Night? . . . Why would your - "

"Decibel!" Tumult's voice snapped in with authority and command,
causing her jump to attention. "We don't have the time for this. You
will return to Deepstryke and let him know we are on our way!"

"Yes sir!" her green and grey frame rigid and stiff, although it was
difficult to tell if it was in anger or military decorum. In either
case she pivoted on a heel and began to march off away from them. 

Tumult turned to look at Darkfate and Nightstrike, "You two, follow
her." his voice still carried the same note of command, although not
quite so loud. "It's time you met Deepstryke."

Preston
